The paper deals with classification of high-dimensional data using a network Lasso approach, which is a popular method in machine learning and statistics. The paper also mentions the use of a primal-dual splitting method, which is commonly used in optimization and signal processing. Based on these keywords and methods, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
